=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sgu1665702731162.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sgu1665702731162.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sgu1665702731162.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sgu1665702731162\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      data types\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify the file containing the data type specification.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"sgu1665702731162__topic_d54470e1_d54471e1_d54472e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sgu1665702731162__p_d54473e1_d54474e1_d54475e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$ODx_PARAMS = data types : '</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">'</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sgu1665702731162__section_plv_4pm_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d251315e66\">Arguments</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sgu1665702731162__p_d54479e1_d54480e1_d54481e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>—name of the file that\n            contains the data type specification, enclosed within matching quotation marks\n               (<code class=\"ph codeph\">'</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>). If the file is not in the current\n            directory, <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var> must include the full path to the file.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"sgu1665702731162__note_zxp_ppm_jcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> USYS: and USYSADM: are permitted in the path and\n            are expanded.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iug1665702954222.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuring ODBC</a><p>Use the Uniface ODBC configuration file generator to generate the ODBC settings required for your assignment file.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531969\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531969\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "data types Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 data types Specify the file containing the data type specification. USYS$ODx_PARAMS = data types : ' FileName ' Arguments FileName —name of the file that contains the data type specification, enclosed within matching quotation marks ( ' or \" ). If the file is not in the current directory, FileName must include the full path to the file. Note: USYS: and USYSADM: are permitted in the path and are expanded. Related Links Configuring ODBC Use the Uniface ODBC configuration file generator to generate the ODBC settings required for your assignment file. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}